1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,810
(Previously)
My name's Leo. I'm your brother.

2
00:00:01,830 --> 00:00:03,883
You two seem close. Are you dating?

3
00:00:04,310 --> 00:00:07,105
So what do I do to make two cats get along?

4
00:00:07,134 --> 00:00:08,392
Cats are like humans.

5
00:00:08,414 --> 00:00:10,160
You need to help them build good memories together.

6
00:00:11,240 --> 00:00:12,181
Let's do this together.

7
00:00:12,203 --> 00:00:13,738
Why do I have to help you?

8
00:00:13,767 --> 00:00:14,858
I'm your friggin' brother.

9
00:00:14,901 --> 00:00:15,869
Just do whatever I tell you.

10
00:00:16,790 --> 00:00:19,287
Yeah!!!!

11
00:00:19,316 --> 00:00:21,752
Tiger. Can I go into Mom's room?

12
00:00:23,960 --> 00:00:26,989
If you're worried about your brother, go talk to him.

13
00:00:28,220 --> 00:00:29,810
Yuck, you smell like cigarettes.

14
00:00:29,847 --> 00:00:33,483
But this smell is what tells you you're not alone anymore.

15
00:00:33,653 --> 00:00:34,555
Happy birthday na.

16
00:00:34,580 --> 00:00:36,698
Thank you for this birthday gift.

17
00:00:45,210 --> 00:00:45,781
Hey!

18
00:00:48,650 --> 00:00:51,461
I'm older. Just do what I say.

19
00:00:51,476 --> 00:00:52,574
When you can't win the argument,

20
00:00:52,603 --> 00:00:53,810
you pull the seniority card, huh?

21
00:00:54,830 --> 00:00:55,890
Calm down, you two.

22
00:00:55,930 --> 00:00:57,738
We just had a bonding party last night.

23
00:00:58,170 --> 00:00:59,236
Didn't that help at all?

24
00:00:59,540 --> 00:01:00,850
I already eased up.

25
00:01:00,887 --> 00:01:02,450
I'm letting him watch the café alone.

26
00:01:02,487 --> 00:01:03,476
Why are you still whining?

27
00:01:03,520 --> 00:01:04,821
You think I don't know?

28
00:01:05,350 --> 00:01:07,752
You're leaving the café to me
because you're going to Korat.

29
00:01:07,774 --> 00:01:09,454
I'm going there to make merit
for Mom's 100-day memorial.

30
00:01:09,483 --> 00:01:12,021
You already took care of the funeral.

31
00:01:12,410 --> 00:01:13,607
It's my turn this time.

32
00:01:14,090 --> 00:01:15,192
You stay here scooping cat litter.

33
00:01:15,229 --> 00:01:16,720
If you just need someone to watch the café,

34
00:01:17,850 --> 00:01:18,850
want me to help out?

35
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:19,600
Good.

36
00:01:19,960 --> 00:01:21,498
You draw lots for us.

37
00:01:21,556 --> 00:01:24,029
Whoever's name comes up
gets to go make merit for Mom.

38
00:01:24,058 --> 00:01:25,600
That's not the kind of help I meant.

39
00:01:25,629 --> 00:01:26,000
Deal.

40
00:01:26,820 --> 00:01:28,916
The winner goes with Tiger.

41
00:01:29,380 --> 00:01:31,549
The loser stays here cleaning cat poop.

42
00:01:40,290 --> 00:01:41,454
I can just watch the café for both of you.

43
00:01:41,483 --> 00:01:42,181
Draw!

44
00:01:54,180 --> 00:01:57,658
PUNARI VILAWONG

45
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:58,436
I knew…

46
00:01:58,710 --> 00:02:00,189
you'd pick me no matter what.

47
00:02:01,610 --> 00:02:05,410
I knew you'd want me to do this, right?

48
00:02:05,432 --> 00:02:07,258
JE MEOW

49
00:02:07,294 --> 00:02:07,985
LYNX / LYNX

50
00:02:08,014 --> 00:02:10,327
I've been such a good little brother to him.

51
00:02:10,356 --> 00:02:12,007
Didn't you really leave anything for me,

52
00:02:12,596 --> 00:02:13,876
besides cat litter duty?

53
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:18,981
The 2-digit lottery would be nice, mom.

54
00:02:21,470 --> 00:02:22,792
Cat-Cheer Café, wel...

55
00:02:31,540 --> 00:02:32,545
Thank you, Mom.

56
00:02:33,350 --> 00:02:34,698
You sent me the jackpot.

57
00:02:41,740 --> 00:02:43,185
How are you while you're here, Mom?

58
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:44,610
Not lonely, I hope.

59
00:02:45,910 --> 00:02:46,887
It's your old stomping grounds after all.

60
00:02:51,850 --> 00:02:52,400
By the way,

61
00:02:54,830 --> 00:02:56,225
I met Leo.

62
00:02:57,710 --> 00:02:58,720
We're doing fine.

63
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:01,760
They really are, Je Meow.

64
00:03:02,270 --> 00:03:05,469
Except they fight every day.

65
00:03:06,110 --> 00:03:08,152
I fight with all your kids, don't I?

66
00:03:08,390 --> 00:03:11,156
Every single one of them's a pain.

67
00:03:11,810 --> 00:03:14,138
Especially the one you said
would be the hardest to crack.

68
00:03:15,450 --> 00:03:16,749
I've experienced that firsthand.

69
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:18,945
Hey.

70
00:03:19,990 --> 00:03:20,909
Who are you talking about?

71
00:03:21,690 --> 00:03:23,192
I mean…

72
00:03:23,610 --> 00:03:25,330
the one your mom promised me.

73
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,607
She said if I could get him
to accept my friend request,

74
00:03:27,629 --> 00:03:30,916
she'd give him to me
plus the cat café.

75
00:03:31,563 --> 00:03:33,560
Now I've got the café.

76
00:03:33,850 --> 00:03:35,098
All that's left is…

77
00:03:35,620 --> 00:03:36,778
Water, Mom.

78
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:39,410
I forgot to bring you water.

79
00:03:40,525 --> 00:03:41,667
Can you go buy it for me?

80
00:03:42,730 --> 00:03:44,189
Changing the subject already, huh?

81
00:03:54,990 --> 00:03:56,109
I know…

82
00:03:56,540 --> 00:03:57,905
If you were still here,

83
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:00,436
you'd be laughing right now, right?

84
00:04:15,100 --> 00:04:18,734
Who told me he'd never have
a lover in this lifetime?

85
00:04:18,756 --> 00:04:19,607
Come on, Mom.

86
00:04:19,643 --> 00:04:22,123
As far back as I can remember,
you were left all alone.

87
00:04:22,152 --> 00:04:23,352
Who would dare have a lover?

88
00:04:24,170 --> 00:04:28,210
And you kept telling me every day
that being alone was best.

89
00:04:28,232 --> 00:04:29,621
You actually believed me?

90
00:04:32,749 --> 00:04:34,312
You can tell, right?

91
00:04:34,334 --> 00:04:35,847
Tiger's a good person.

92
00:04:35,883 --> 00:04:37,134
He's so good that…

93
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:39,301
I don't want him to make a bad choice,

94
00:04:41,045 --> 00:04:42,591
like you did with Dad.

95
00:04:45,370 --> 00:04:48,400
If you were still here, I'd want to ask you...

96
00:04:49,990 --> 00:04:52,225
how can a kid born from a mistake like me

97
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:56,480
be a good partner to someone?

98
00:04:58,014 --> 00:04:59,250
Why are you back already?

99
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:00,945
I'm not done talking to Mom.

100
00:05:06,030 --> 00:05:06,930
Hi.

101
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,500
"Cat for Cash"
(Episode 6)

102
00:06:14,030 --> 00:06:15,992
Have you been to Korat before?

103
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:19,112
This is my first time here.

104
00:06:19,550 --> 00:06:23,745
Grandpa Petch keeps
his parents' ashes at this temple.

105
00:06:24,040 --> 00:06:26,261
So he brought your mom's ashes here too.

106
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:29,818
Have you two eaten yet?

107
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:31,861
We already had a little something.

108
00:06:32,170 --> 00:06:33,265
That's good.

109
00:06:33,301 --> 00:06:35,076
Then come eat at our place.

110
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:35,840
Right, honey?

111
00:06:35,869 --> 00:06:37,323
Since you're already here.

112
00:06:37,690 --> 00:06:38,240
Okay?

113
00:06:38,276 --> 00:06:39,490
Thank you, Grandma.

114
00:06:39,510 --> 00:06:41,396
But we should head back
and look after the café.

115
00:06:41,556 --> 00:06:43,883
Come on. Stop by just for a bit.

116
00:06:43,912 --> 00:06:45,563
It's not far from here.

117
00:06:45,585 --> 00:06:46,334
It won't take long.

118
00:06:46,487 --> 00:06:47,389
Come on, honey.

119
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,520
Let them head back and rest.

120
00:06:52,290 --> 00:06:52,989
Oh, sorry.

121
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:55,970
Alright then, have a safe trip home.

122
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,101
Grandpa Petch,

123
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:00,887
where's your house?

124
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:06,152
I think Lynx would love to try
Grandma's cooking.

125
00:07:09,850 --> 00:07:12,770
Don't you want to see
the house your mom grew up in?

126
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:23,025
Lynx never mentioned
he had a younger brother.

127
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:26,116
I'm his half-brother.

128
00:07:27,570 --> 00:07:29,570
Lynx never mentioned

129
00:07:29,607 --> 00:07:31,105
having such a good-looking vet...

130
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:34,909
I mean, such a dedicated vet.

131
00:07:36,860 --> 00:07:38,530
Granny Juu's pretty old.

132
00:07:38,552 --> 00:07:40,640
Je Meow asked me
to check on her every month.

133
00:07:41,450 --> 00:07:43,505
How about food?

134
00:07:43,549 --> 00:07:44,785
Are you asking me out?

135
00:07:45,190 --> 00:07:46,261
You can pick the place.

136
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,509
I meant Granny Juu.

137
00:07:48,552 --> 00:07:50,014
Is she eating normally?

138
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,330
Oh.

139
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:54,720
Yeah, she is.

140
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:57,236
Then there's nothing to worry about.

141
00:07:57,770 --> 00:07:59,280
This month you pass, Granny Juu.

142
00:08:01,630 --> 00:08:04,916
Since you're here,

143
00:08:06,010 --> 00:08:07,570
can I treat you to dessert?

144
00:08:08,410 --> 00:08:10,843
I'll take a bread with
butter and condensed milk.

145
00:08:12,690 --> 00:08:13,381
Krapor.
Yes?

146
00:08:14,043 --> 00:08:15,069
What are you doing here?

147
00:08:15,512 --> 00:08:17,510
I never miss free food.

148
00:08:18,538 --> 00:08:21,789
Dr. Pom, how's Granny Juu
doing this month?

149
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:25,214
She's in good health
for a 15-year-old cat.

150
00:08:25,350 --> 00:08:27,890
Whoa, 15 years?

151
00:08:29,390 --> 00:08:33,454
I heard one cat year
equals four human years.

152
00:08:33,498 --> 00:08:35,665
If there's anything
you want to do for her, do it now.

153
00:08:35,694 --> 00:08:36,770
Don't make her wait.

154
00:08:37,789 --> 00:08:39,709
If there's anything
I want to do for her…

155
00:08:42,020 --> 00:08:44,705
Does finding her
a grandson-in-law count?

156
00:08:46,850 --> 00:08:48,000
I've got an idea.

157
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:51,323
Can you wait here for me?

158
00:08:51,352 --> 00:08:52,349
I'll be right back.

159
00:08:52,385 --> 00:08:55,600
I'm sure Granny Juu's
gonna love this.

160
00:09:06,330 --> 00:09:07,716
Look who's here.

161
00:09:11,141 --> 00:09:12,545
Who's here?

162
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:14,072
Come on in, kids.

163
00:09:14,970 --> 00:09:16,145
Hi again.

164
00:09:16,150 --> 00:09:17,309
PRESIDENT OF THE KORAT
CAT OWNERS ASSOCIATION

165
00:09:17,345 --> 00:09:20,690
Grandpa Petch is the president of the
Korat Cat Owners Association.

166
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:21,570
Oh.

167
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:23,978
Come on up.

168
00:09:25,470 --> 00:09:26,640
Make yourselves at home.

169
00:09:27,930 --> 00:09:30,923
(Who's that? He looks like Meow.)

170
00:09:31,374 --> 00:09:33,370
He's Meow's son.

171
00:09:34,645 --> 00:09:37,115
(That means he's your grandson.)

172
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:40,290
(Can he talk to us like you do?)

173
00:09:42,090 --> 00:09:44,683
You're wondering, huh?

174
00:09:46,014 --> 00:09:48,010
Let's find out.

175
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:11,876
How is it?

176
00:10:12,420 --> 00:10:13,483
Can you eat it?

177
00:10:13,512 --> 00:10:15,040
It's really delicious.

178
00:10:18,590 --> 00:10:20,320
How's the café doing?

179
00:10:23,430 --> 00:10:24,821
It's doing well, Grandpa.

180
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:28,436
How's the cat association?

181
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:30,138
It's doing well too.

182
00:10:37,250 --> 00:10:39,789
You've got to try my omelet.

183
00:10:39,832 --> 00:10:40,901
It's not just a simple omelet, you know.

184
00:10:40,923 --> 00:10:41,985
No one makes it like I do.

185
00:10:44,220 --> 00:10:45,578
Give me some.

186
00:10:46,510 --> 00:10:48,676
I have it every day,
and it's always delicious.

187
00:10:51,876 --> 00:10:52,712
Thank you.

188
00:11:11,220 --> 00:11:12,741
No, Lynx, just leave it.

189
00:11:12,770 --> 00:11:14,160
Let your grandpa clean up.

190
00:11:14,210 --> 00:11:15,600
You come with me.

191
00:11:15,643 --> 00:11:17,301
I've got something to show you.

192
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:19,301
Come on.
Okay.

193
00:11:51,770 --> 00:11:52,603
Grandpa Petch.

194
00:11:52,970 --> 00:11:53,781
Hm?

195
00:11:55,060 --> 00:11:56,480
That piano is yours?

196
00:11:57,060 --> 00:11:57,556
No.

197
00:12:02,140 --> 00:12:05,978
So you've been helping Lynx at the café,

198
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:08,829
are you two friends?

199
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:14,101
Well… not exactly.

200
00:12:14,530 --> 00:12:15,192
We…

201
00:12:15,610 --> 00:12:19,730
(Looks like they're dating for sure.)

202
00:12:20,060 --> 00:12:22,269
No, I'm just his creditor.

203
00:12:23,340 --> 00:12:27,541
(What? Don't tell me he can hear me too?)

204
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:37,527
How did my family's secret
end up with you?

205
00:12:44,580 --> 00:12:45,985
What's taking Krapor so long?

206
00:12:52,950 --> 00:12:57,709
Yeah, we've been waiting forever.

207
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:01,694
It's not a bad thing though.

208
00:13:02,210 --> 00:13:04,538
I should treat him to a meal to thank him.

209
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:09,032
I'm back.

210
00:13:09,870 --> 00:13:11,920
Sorry to keep you waiting.

211
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:15,672
Krapor.
Yeah?

212
00:13:16,363 --> 00:13:17,243
What did you bring?

213
00:13:17,910 --> 00:13:18,676
You guys,

214
00:13:19,160 --> 00:13:21,832
do you know what old folks want most,

215
00:13:21,883 --> 00:13:24,720
but their kids can't give them?

216
00:13:25,430 --> 00:13:26,261
What is it?

217
00:13:26,780 --> 00:13:29,410
It's… time.

218
00:13:30,050 --> 00:13:32,814
That sounds kind of familiar.

219
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:34,603
Isn't that from How to Make
Millions Before “Grandmeow” Dies?

220
00:13:34,625 --> 00:13:35,381
Grandma!

221
00:13:36,380 --> 00:13:39,134
Granny Juu had babies once.

222
00:13:39,192 --> 00:13:42,516
Je Meow gave one to my mom.

223
00:13:42,552 --> 00:13:45,636
So I brought her child here
so they could spend time together.

224
00:13:45,672 --> 00:13:47,512
They can have a happy reunion.

225
00:13:48,070 --> 00:13:49,076
Hold on, Krapor.

226
00:13:49,530 --> 00:13:50,530
What's wrong?

227
00:13:51,570 --> 00:13:52,887
They might fight.

228
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,781
No, they won't.

229
00:13:55,811 --> 00:13:57,062
They're mother and child.

230
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:58,618
They'll definitely recognize each other.

231
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:07,207
Hey, AJ. What's gotten into you?

232
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:08,909
That's your mom.

233
00:14:08,945 --> 00:14:10,560
I told you.

234
00:14:10,610 --> 00:14:12,203
Cats recognize each other by scent.

235
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,381
When the scent changes,

236
00:14:13,418 --> 00:14:15,380
they can't recognize
even their own mom and dad.

237
00:14:15,990 --> 00:14:18,465
And that's the end of my Grandmeow story.

238
00:14:19,370 --> 00:14:20,276
What a bummer.

239
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:29,527
Your mom was a smart student.

240
00:14:29,790 --> 00:14:31,367
She was at the
top of her class every year.

241
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:34,901
Every day, she'd just bury
herself in books in this room.

242
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:40,218
I can't picture that.

243
00:14:40,490 --> 00:14:43,054
All I remember is Mom buried in the couch,

244
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:47,629
drinking beer and
watching melodramas day in day out.

245
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:50,567
Deep down, she probably
wanted that kind of life.

246
00:14:50,610 --> 00:14:52,450
But she felt obligated to your grandpa.

247
00:14:52,472 --> 00:14:55,098
One time, she snuck out
to play games with her friends.

248
00:14:55,141 --> 00:14:56,378
Grandpa caught her.

249
00:14:56,710 --> 00:14:58,654
He dragged her home
and beat her with a cane,

250
00:14:58,676 --> 00:14:59,738
and she ended up with a fever.

251
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:07,127
How did a top student like Mom
end up with Dad?

252
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,789
She never told you anything about that?

253
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:11,629
She told me that...

254
00:15:12,060 --> 00:15:14,734
Dad was a senior who gave her
advice about grad school.

255
00:15:15,910 --> 00:15:17,520
She was kind of innocent,

256
00:15:18,060 --> 00:15:19,614
and he got her drunk.

257
00:15:21,490 --> 00:15:24,465
Actually, she wasn't really that innocent.

258
00:15:28,650 --> 00:15:31,243
She was smart like Grandpa,

259
00:15:31,287 --> 00:15:33,883
but boy-crazy just like me
when I was young.

260
00:15:36,580 --> 00:15:40,138
But Mom always told me
she didn't care about love.

261
00:15:40,661 --> 00:15:41,403
Really?

262
00:15:42,270 --> 00:15:43,963
She just didn't say what she really felt.

263
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,738
If she didn't care about it,

264
00:15:45,781 --> 00:15:47,978
you wouldn't be here.

265
00:15:48,330 --> 00:15:51,818
Even though things didn't work out
between your mom and dad,

266
00:15:51,861 --> 00:15:55,214
it was definitely love in the beginning.

267
00:16:01,430 --> 00:16:03,621
There's a lot you don't know.

268
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:06,967
I've kept all her stuff in this room.

269
00:16:07,390 --> 00:16:09,920
Take your time getting to know her.

270
00:16:11,450 --> 00:16:11,985
Alright.

271
00:16:41,090 --> 00:16:43,090
I was the last person with Je Meow.

272
00:16:44,710 --> 00:16:47,992
I remember she whispered
something in my ear.

273
00:16:49,150 --> 00:16:50,792
Next thing I knew,

274
00:16:51,990 --> 00:16:53,461
I could hear cats talking.

275
00:16:56,770 --> 00:16:58,858
It's a power transfer.

276
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:02,465
We can communicate with cats.

277
00:17:04,230 --> 00:17:07,985
This power only gets passed down
to blood relatives.

278
00:17:09,220 --> 00:17:11,018
Even Grandma Tam doesn't have it.

279
00:17:14,190 --> 00:17:18,218
I think Je Meow wanted
to pass it on to Lynx,

280
00:17:18,790 --> 00:17:19,869
but…

281
00:17:20,690 --> 00:17:21,701
she didn't get the chance.

282
00:17:23,260 --> 00:17:24,807
But I can pass it back to Lynx now.

283
00:17:26,150 --> 00:17:27,556
You can't just easily pass it back.

284
00:17:29,220 --> 00:17:34,850
And this power can only
be transferred once.

285
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:43,069
I already transferred it to Meow.

286
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,120
So that means…

287
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:49,061
I'm the only one
who can pass it on to Lynx?

288
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:51,738
Let me go get him.
Hold on.

289
00:17:54,312 --> 00:17:59,403
Only someone who truly loves cats
can use this power.

290
00:18:00,180 --> 00:18:01,898
Do you think Lynx is ready?

291
00:18:04,515 --> 00:18:05,973
I'm not sure.

292
00:18:07,710 --> 00:18:09,112
But don't worry.

293
00:18:09,963 --> 00:18:11,960
I'll keep this power safe

294
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:13,498
and won't give it to anyone else.

295
00:18:13,534 --> 00:18:14,901
(Can we trust him?)

296
00:18:14,945 --> 00:18:19,549
(To be sure, make him marry Lynx now.)

297
00:18:19,592 --> 00:18:20,436
No need to go that far yet.

298
00:18:20,472 --> 00:18:22,909
(Why?! You don't like our Lynx?)

299
00:18:22,952 --> 00:18:24,690
It's not like that. Well, I…

300
00:18:24,734 --> 00:18:25,294
Hey!

301
00:18:25,820 --> 00:18:29,570
So how do you feel about my grandson?

302
00:18:36,650 --> 00:18:37,600
I like Lynx.

303
00:18:41,380 --> 00:18:42,356
Will that be okay with you?

304
00:18:47,690 --> 00:18:48,807
At least…

305
00:18:51,350 --> 00:18:54,320
you've got the guts
to admit your true feelings,

306
00:18:56,550 --> 00:18:58,007
unlike Lynx's dad.

307
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:01,258
You don't have to worry at all.

308
00:19:02,660 --> 00:19:03,789
I promise

309
00:19:04,490 --> 00:19:06,000
I'll make Lynx love cats

310
00:19:06,529 --> 00:19:08,000
and he'll be able to talk to them eventually.

311
00:19:13,150 --> 00:19:14,603
Now I understand

312
00:19:16,600 --> 00:19:19,578
why my daughter gave this power to you.

313
00:19:35,410 --> 00:19:36,814
Excuse me, Mom.

314
00:19:39,830 --> 00:19:42,356
(The Diary of Maew Meow's Journey)

315
00:19:42,820 --> 00:19:46,523
(First day of my uni life – Dad dropping
me off and picking me up like a kid.)

316
00:19:46,970 --> 00:19:49,323
(Good news, Dad's letting me
go to Loy Krathong.)

317
00:19:49,352 --> 00:19:52,814
(Bad news, Dad's deadline is 6 PM.)

318
00:19:53,060 --> 00:19:55,556
(If I end up single, it's his fault.)

319
00:19:56,880 --> 00:20:00,930
(Woohoo, I finally snuck out to watch
a movie with my uni friends for the first time.)

320
00:20:00,967 --> 00:20:04,021
(The scene where the heroine plays
“Canon” on the piano was so romantic.)

321
00:20:04,540 --> 00:20:07,512
When you were with me,
all I ever saw you play was money pool.

322
00:20:10,840 --> 00:20:13,076
"THE HUNT FOR 9 CATS"

323
00:20:14,284 --> 00:20:19,284
(Yay! Dad finally let me stay over
with my friends to celebrate graduation.)

324
00:20:19,323 --> 00:20:25,025
(Since Korat is the city of cats,
we're going to find all 9 cats on this trip.)

325
00:20:25,054 --> 00:20:28,741
(Whoever finishes this trip together
will be friends until old age…)

326
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:31,323
(Like a cat's 9 lives.)

327
00:21:21,060 --> 00:21:23,200
Someone left this Canon sheet music here.

328
00:21:23,670 --> 00:21:25,396
So I played it.

329
00:21:30,470 --> 00:21:31,840
I know who left it.

330
00:21:39,270 --> 00:21:42,443
Mom once planned a trip to
search for cats around Korat with friends.

331
00:21:44,750 --> 00:21:46,029
But she never got to go

332
00:21:47,380 --> 00:21:48,712
because she had me.

333
00:21:52,870 --> 00:21:54,603
Since we're already here,

334
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:56,647
how about we go find those cats for her?

335
00:21:57,030 --> 00:21:57,847
Can we do that?

336
00:21:58,310 --> 00:21:59,221
Why not?

337
00:21:59,830 --> 00:22:01,636
You still owe me a date, remember?

338
00:22:16,060 --> 00:22:17,752
Take care of yourself.

339
00:22:17,781 --> 00:22:19,403
Come visit us some time.

340
00:22:20,010 --> 00:22:20,494
Yes, Grandma.

341
00:22:20,560 --> 00:22:23,498
Here. I made extra for you two.

342
00:22:25,220 --> 00:22:26,370
Thank you so much.

343
00:22:27,740 --> 00:22:29,360
Please excuse us then.

344
00:22:31,310 --> 00:22:32,029
Goodbye.

345
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:33,614
Have a safe trip.

346
00:22:37,280 --> 00:22:38,254
Please take care.

347
00:22:38,552 --> 00:22:39,832
Thanks.

348
00:22:44,910 --> 00:22:46,712
CHOMPHON GATE

349
00:22:53,190 --> 00:22:54,050
Before anything else,

350
00:22:54,072 --> 00:22:55,330
we should pay our respects here.

351
00:22:57,590 --> 00:23:01,978
May this trip help us find all 9 cats.

352
00:23:04,810 --> 00:23:06,800
They say after you pay your respects,

353
00:23:06,836 --> 00:23:08,334
you walk through the gate and make a wish.

354
00:23:08,580 --> 00:23:09,978
If you walk 1 round,

355
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:11,578
you'll come back to Korat again.

356
00:23:11,621 --> 00:23:12,472
That's nice.

357
00:23:12,810 --> 00:23:14,276
Your grandparents would be happy.

358
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:16,538
If you walk 2 rounds,

359
00:23:17,070 --> 00:23:18,400
you'll get a job in Korat.

360
00:23:18,429 --> 00:23:19,498
This one's nice too.

361
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:22,247
If the café fails,
we can find jobs here.

362
00:23:23,090 --> 00:23:24,850
If you walk 3 rounds…

363
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:27,949
What happens?

364
00:23:30,070 --> 00:23:31,389
You'll get a lover from Korat.

365
00:23:33,750 --> 00:23:34,945
You were born here.

366
00:23:36,150 --> 00:23:37,636
Does that count as being from Korat?

367
00:23:42,630 --> 00:23:43,687
We should get going,

368
00:23:43,730 --> 00:23:44,850
or we won't find all 9 cats.

369
00:24:18,763 --> 00:24:21,570
(This trip starts with a local cat breed.)

370
00:24:29,640 --> 00:24:31,600
(Cat No. 2 is an indie teen cat.)

371
00:24:31,643 --> 00:24:33,600
(Never stays inside the box.)

372
00:24:39,130 --> 00:24:42,123
(Cat No. 3 is a beauty queen cat.)

373
00:24:42,589 --> 00:24:44,590
(So gorgeous, it earned a crown.)

374
00:24:46,363 --> 00:24:49,592
(Cat No. 4 is a flirty cat.)

375
00:24:50,450 --> 00:24:52,450
(Loves using bridges to get closer.)

376
00:24:55,800 --> 00:24:59,490
(Cats No. 5 and 6
are on Cat Walking Street.)

377
00:25:00,280 --> 00:25:04,261
(One's the big boss,
the other's the baby of the gang.)

378
00:25:04,870 --> 00:25:08,370
(Cat No. 7 is a shy cat.)

379
00:25:08,392 --> 00:25:11,709
(It likes to play hide-and-seek
on this mountain.)

380
00:25:12,100 --> 00:25:15,381
Is this one a statue or a painting?

381
00:25:17,210 --> 00:25:18,320
I'm not sure either.

382
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:21,789
But Mom drew it like this.

383
00:25:23,050 --> 00:25:24,341
It's somewhere on this mountain.

384
00:25:24,378 --> 00:25:25,272
Let's go up and see.

385
00:25:30,390 --> 00:25:32,123
You really didn't have to walk me back.

386
00:25:32,470 --> 00:25:34,007
I feel bad making Krapor

387
00:25:34,036 --> 00:25:36,010
watch the café for you.

388
00:25:36,996 --> 00:25:37,992
I had to.

389
00:25:38,460 --> 00:25:41,309
You came all this way
to check on Granny Juu.

390
00:25:45,310 --> 00:25:47,032
Being a cat is kind of sad, isn't it?

391
00:25:47,450 --> 00:25:49,563
They can't even recognize
their own kittens.

392
00:25:52,730 --> 00:25:54,480
I'm actually jealous of Granny Juu.

393
00:25:56,385 --> 00:25:57,061
Why?

394
00:26:00,280 --> 00:26:02,523
My parents split while
I was still in the womb.

395
00:26:04,750 --> 00:26:05,992
Not long after I was born,

396
00:26:06,830 --> 00:26:09,578
before I could meet my dad, he died.

397
00:26:11,530 --> 00:26:13,265
At least Granny Juu and her child

398
00:26:13,720 --> 00:26:15,243
had some time together.

399
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:21,985
If I ever ran into my dad somewhere,

400
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:24,894
we probably wouldn't
even recognize each other,

401
00:26:26,989 --> 00:26:28,567
just like Granny Juu and her child now.

402
00:26:32,990 --> 00:26:35,578
Then tonight, after you close the café,

403
00:26:35,621 --> 00:26:37,578
can you bring Granny Juu
and her child to my clinic?

404
00:26:37,990 --> 00:26:40,967
I might have a way
to keep them from fighting.

405
00:27:06,410 --> 00:27:07,483
I looked everywhere.

406
00:27:08,130 --> 00:27:09,738
I didn't see a cat like what your mom drew.

407
00:27:10,290 --> 00:27:12,967
Yeah, I looked through that side.

408
00:27:13,010 --> 00:27:13,898
I couldn't find one either.

409
00:27:22,020 --> 00:27:24,509
Actually, Mom drew this ages ago.

410
00:27:25,300 --> 00:27:27,112
It might not be here anymore.

411
00:27:34,950 --> 00:27:35,941
Watch your head.

412
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:45,149
You okay, right?

413
00:27:47,660 --> 00:27:48,480
Ouch.

414
00:27:50,760 --> 00:27:51,316
What's wrong?

415
00:27:51,347 --> 00:27:52,940
Leg cramp.

416
00:27:56,090 --> 00:27:58,480
Then let's rest here for a bit.

417
00:28:03,270 --> 00:28:04,101
Have some water.

418
00:28:14,700 --> 00:28:17,920
You're not playing hard to get anymore?

419
00:28:20,630 --> 00:28:22,421
And you're not asking
for permission anymore either.

420
00:28:29,810 --> 00:28:30,800
Feeling better now?

421
00:28:35,294 --> 00:28:35,694
Yes.

422
00:28:47,490 --> 00:28:48,160
Lynx.

423
00:28:49,140 --> 00:28:50,923
Let me see your mom's drawing again.

424
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:07,665
The cave opening is the cat ears.

425
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:11,098
And the railings are the whiskers.

426
00:29:12,010 --> 00:29:14,829
Yeah. You're right.

427
00:29:18,240 --> 00:29:19,360
Take pictures for me.

428
00:29:31,900 --> 00:29:33,083
“They say…

429
00:29:33,112 --> 00:29:35,374
if you ask someone to be your lover here,

430
00:29:35,890 --> 00:29:36,807
it'll come true.”

431
00:29:45,898 --> 00:29:50,800
“I can only dream that someday
someone will bring me up here.”

432
00:29:59,900 --> 00:30:01,301
I'm sorry for you, Mom.

433
00:30:02,390 --> 00:30:04,567
Real life wasn't as romantic
as you dreamed.

434
00:30:17,910 --> 00:30:20,472
Since you're chasing these cats
to make your mother's dream come true,

435
00:30:22,378 --> 00:30:24,380
don't you want to help fulfill
another dream of hers too?

436
00:30:36,380 --> 00:30:40,130
After this trip, let's become boyfriends.

437
00:31:02,823 --> 00:31:06,087
PHA KEP TAWAN, THAP LAN NATIONAL PARK

438
00:31:06,123 --> 00:31:07,090
We're here.

439
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:09,287
Cat No.8 is on this cliff.

440
00:31:10,170 --> 00:31:11,665
Mom wrote it here...

441
00:31:12,100 --> 00:31:14,269
“Cat No. 8 is a sleepy black cat.”

442
00:31:14,654 --> 00:31:16,650
“It only shows up at sunset.”

443
00:31:18,970 --> 00:31:20,530
It's right there.

444
00:31:23,420 --> 00:31:24,523
Look at the shadow.

445
00:31:24,980 --> 00:31:26,727
It looks just like the sleeping cat
your mom drew.

446
00:31:27,750 --> 00:31:28,589
You're right.

447
00:31:29,150 --> 00:31:32,523
But this one has ears.

448
00:31:37,010 --> 00:31:39,985
Then let's add ears to it.

449
00:31:40,700 --> 00:31:41,403
Okay.

450
00:31:59,500 --> 00:32:02,800
Now I get why they call it Sunset Cliff.

451
00:32:09,180 --> 00:32:10,174
What's wrong?

452
00:32:10,980 --> 00:32:11,927
Isn't it beautiful?

453
00:32:15,130 --> 00:32:18,770
I've always thought that I was the
reason why my mom's life fell apart.

454
00:32:20,186 --> 00:32:23,840
If I hadn't been born,
she might still be here.

455
00:32:24,290 --> 00:32:25,978
She would've stayed with
Grandpa and Grandma.

456
00:32:27,050 --> 00:32:29,687
Maybe some decent guy
would've asked her out and

457
00:32:31,330 --> 00:32:33,330
taken her to watch
a beautiful sunset like this.

458
00:32:39,810 --> 00:32:40,698
You know what?

459
00:32:42,230 --> 00:32:43,629
Your grandpa said…

460
00:32:44,760 --> 00:32:46,327
you have something like your mom.

461
00:32:47,140 --> 00:32:48,152
But I think…

462
00:32:49,066 --> 00:32:52,948
it's actually something of hers
that is still in you.

463
00:32:57,200 --> 00:32:58,741
You didn't ruin her life.

464
00:32:59,860 --> 00:33:01,985
But you made her…
still alive in this world.

465
00:33:02,014 --> 00:33:07,156
♪ I told you I love you, love you ♪

466
00:33:07,192 --> 00:33:08,632
Every place you go,

467
00:33:09,770 --> 00:33:11,229
everything you see,

468
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:15,069
I believe your mom
is always there with you.

469
00:33:15,098 --> 00:33:19,992
♪ In the arms that embraced, in the smiles I gave ♪

470
00:33:20,014 --> 00:33:25,985
♪ In every little thing I did for you each day ♪

471
00:33:26,029 --> 00:33:32,000
♪ I told you I love you, love you ♪

472
00:33:32,036 --> 00:33:37,978
♪ From that day I've stayed the same ♪

473
00:33:38,021 --> 00:33:43,978
♪ I'm sorry I can't say I love you in words ♪

474
00:33:44,014 --> 00:33:50,334
♪ But someday you'll understand every word ♪

475
00:33:50,356 --> 00:33:53,541
♪ Every word ♪

476
00:34:02,060 --> 00:34:02,945
Dr. Pom.

477
00:34:02,974 --> 00:34:04,290
I brought Granny Juu and her child.

478
00:34:05,780 --> 00:34:06,821
This way.

479
00:34:06,843 --> 00:34:08,080
I've set up a room for them.

480
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:09,556
What?

481
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:13,214
Won't they fight
if they're in the same room?

482
00:34:13,250 --> 00:34:14,807
Remember what you told me?

483
00:34:14,843 --> 00:34:17,112
If you met your dad somewhere,

484
00:34:17,141 --> 00:34:18,530
you wouldn't recognize each other.

485
00:34:20,140 --> 00:34:21,934
When Granny Juu met
her child at the café,

486
00:34:21,963 --> 00:34:23,956
the place was full of her scent,

487
00:34:23,992 --> 00:34:25,330
so her child got scared.

488
00:34:25,367 --> 00:34:26,676
So I thought

489
00:34:26,727 --> 00:34:32,283
if we bring them somewhere new
where neither of their scents is around,

490
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:34,181
maybe they won't fight.

491
00:34:39,630 --> 00:34:40,341
Lynx.
Did you get anything?

492
00:34:41,323 --> 00:34:42,487
I've got bad news.

493
00:34:43,730 --> 00:34:45,767
The owner of the last cat
went down to run errands.

494
00:34:46,181 --> 00:34:47,658
He will probably come back
tomorrow morning.

495
00:34:48,270 --> 00:34:50,763
What do we do then?

496
00:34:51,160 --> 00:34:52,400
It's already dark.

497
00:34:53,060 --> 00:34:54,683
If we go back,
we should leave now.

498
00:34:56,170 --> 00:34:57,163
Or else…

499
00:35:04,060 --> 00:35:06,938
Lucky they have a tent for rent here.

500
00:35:08,420 --> 00:35:11,978
And lucky you just happened
to pack extra clothes in your trunk.

501
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:17,207
I only brought them
to change during the trip.

502
00:35:17,910 --> 00:35:20,014
I didn't actually plan
to stay overnight with you.

503
00:35:21,352 --> 00:35:22,218
Whatever.

504
00:35:22,400 --> 00:35:24,850
I'm the one who asked you
to come up here anyway.

505
00:35:26,400 --> 00:35:30,138
Let's see what your grandpa
cooked for us.

506
00:35:36,600 --> 00:35:37,527
Wow.

507
00:35:46,705 --> 00:35:48,710
It looks like Korat stir-fried noodles
that Mom used to make.

508
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:53,920
Tonight we survived
thanks to your grandpa.

509
00:35:57,790 --> 00:35:58,312
Wow.

510
00:35:59,950 --> 00:36:03,832
Honestly, I felt bad too.

511
00:36:06,021 --> 00:36:08,020
They even invited us over for a meal.

512
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:09,992
We barely talked at the table.

513
00:36:14,341 --> 00:36:16,340
Like eating with strangers,

514
00:36:17,830 --> 00:36:19,672
rather than family.

515
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:32,320
It smells just like Mom's stir-fried noodles.

516
00:36:33,770 --> 00:36:35,476
Lynx told me…

517
00:36:36,380 --> 00:36:39,360
Meow made stir-fried noodles for him a lot.

518
00:36:41,020 --> 00:36:44,872
That means she remembered
what you taught her.

519
00:36:47,338 --> 00:36:49,340
Scent is like a cat's memory.

520
00:36:49,990 --> 00:36:54,247
When cats are apart so long
they can't remember the old scent.

521
00:36:54,580 --> 00:36:56,654
You just need to let them create
a new memory

522
00:36:57,760 --> 00:36:59,440
until they become the same scent again.

523
00:37:00,010 --> 00:37:01,643
It tastes exactly like Mom's too.

524
00:37:01,701 --> 00:37:06,007
♪ It must be you who healed my heart again ♪

525
00:37:06,043 --> 00:37:08,756
♪ Used to ache with pain ♪

526
00:37:08,814 --> 00:37:15,330
♪ It feels so good now with you by my side ♪

527
00:37:15,367 --> 00:37:20,240
♪ I'll hold you close, won't let go, won't let it fade ♪

528
00:37:20,276 --> 00:37:23,585
♪ This warm and steady space you made ♪

529
00:37:23,629 --> 00:37:33,076
♪ 'Cause it's you, I found my home ♪

530
00:37:39,080 --> 00:37:39,992
Here, Lynx.

531
00:37:40,170 --> 00:37:41,287
Let me rub this balm on your leg.

532
00:37:42,580 --> 00:37:45,338
It's okay. I can do it myself.

533
00:37:49,060 --> 00:37:49,549
Let me.

534
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:50,676
No, thanks.

535
00:37:50,940 --> 00:37:51,498
Hey.

536
00:38:07,420 --> 00:38:08,363
What's wrong?

537
00:38:08,880 --> 00:38:10,690
It's not like we haven't stayed over
together before.

538
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:16,260
Yeah, but we usually have
a bunch of cats around.

539
00:38:22,030 --> 00:38:23,956
I'm not the kind of guy
who takes advantage.

540
00:38:24,980 --> 00:38:28,298
My dad said the same thing to Mom
the first night they stayed together.

541
00:38:28,650 --> 00:38:29,694
Look what happened.

542
00:38:30,150 --> 00:38:31,287
They had me.

543
00:38:32,520 --> 00:38:33,680
Let's be boyfriends first.

544
00:38:33,723 --> 00:38:34,836
Then you can worry about that.

545
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:52,749
Can I ask you something?

546
00:38:55,500 --> 00:38:57,040
Why do you want to be my boyfriend?

547
00:39:01,990 --> 00:39:03,425
You're like a cat, I guess?

548
00:39:06,230 --> 00:39:07,265
Be serious.

549
00:39:20,150 --> 00:39:21,658
When you want a cat,

550
00:39:23,030 --> 00:39:24,661
do you need a reason

551
00:39:27,540 --> 00:39:28,836
other than how cute it is?

552
00:39:39,900 --> 00:39:40,923
But you know what?

553
00:39:42,043 --> 00:39:44,040
I never planned on
having a partner in this life.

554
00:39:47,190 --> 00:39:48,349
What's with that?

555
00:39:49,590 --> 00:39:52,305
I'm definitely not the first person
in the world to hit on you.

556
00:39:53,880 --> 00:39:56,429
If you were born with
a womanizer for a dad

557
00:39:57,832 --> 00:39:59,830
and a mom who gave up on love,

558
00:40:02,420 --> 00:40:04,000
you'd think the same way.

559
00:40:06,100 --> 00:40:07,527
No, I think of it differently.

560
00:40:09,350 --> 00:40:11,505
What my parents couldn't give me,

561
00:40:13,610 --> 00:40:15,025
I'll make it happen myself.

562
00:40:28,390 --> 00:40:32,974
Honestly, I used to think
I was born by mistake,

563
00:40:36,380 --> 00:40:37,585
until I came here.

564
00:40:38,090 --> 00:40:41,614
I learned that Mom once
had a beautiful love too,

565
00:40:45,260 --> 00:40:47,112
even if it didn't last long.

566
00:40:47,934 --> 00:40:49,287
If it does exist,

567
00:40:51,860 --> 00:40:53,629
I want to experience it once too.

568
00:41:33,820 --> 00:41:34,974
What are you doing?

569
00:41:35,450 --> 00:41:37,134
Didn't you say you're not the type
to take advantage?

570
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:39,992
I can't stand seeing a cat shiver.

571
00:41:45,670 --> 00:41:47,156
Are you not okay…

572
00:41:49,280 --> 00:41:52,283
with me being like this?

573
00:42:04,850 --> 00:42:06,312
If you want to hug me,

574
00:42:08,230 --> 00:42:09,541
you can't be just anyone.

575
00:43:16,230 --> 00:43:17,410
Come back and visit again.

576
00:43:18,270 --> 00:43:19,309
Thank you.

577
00:43:20,060 --> 00:43:20,967
Have a safe trip.
Thank you.

578
00:43:23,550 --> 00:43:26,647
I just found out each national park
has its own signature stamp.

579
00:43:26,690 --> 00:43:27,430
THE LAST CAT WILL BE SIGNED
BY A NATIONAL PARK OFFICER.

580
00:43:27,480 --> 00:43:30,334
Congrats on finally collecting all 9 cats.

581
00:43:32,860 --> 00:43:34,341
Mom said

582
00:43:34,820 --> 00:43:37,090
whoever collects all 9 cats together

583
00:43:37,585 --> 00:43:39,590
will be friends until old age.

584
00:43:41,830 --> 00:43:43,098
Who are you calling a friend?

585
00:43:47,670 --> 00:43:48,887
I'm your boyfriend.

586
00:44:02,647 --> 00:44:04,334
And I'll be that until we're old.

587
00:44:28,950 --> 00:44:29,592
(Next Episode)
How's everything?

588
00:44:29,621 --> 00:44:30,916
I heard what happened here.

589
00:44:30,952 --> 00:44:32,654
So those guys were looking for you, Leo?

590
00:44:32,676 --> 00:44:34,334
I shouldn't have let you stay.

591
00:44:34,363 --> 00:44:35,221
Who are you to say that?

592
00:44:35,250 --> 00:44:36,334
You think you're so damn righteous…

593
00:44:36,378 --> 00:44:37,498
If you weren't the only family I had left,

594
00:44:37,527 --> 00:44:39,032
I never would've set foot in this place.

595
00:44:39,069 --> 00:44:40,240
Have you talked to Leo yet?

596
00:44:40,290 --> 00:44:40,989
Not yet.

597
00:44:41,310 --> 00:44:42,225
- Our dad's not dead.
- WICHIEN 08140199773
What do you want to do now?

598
00:44:42,690 --> 00:44:43,650
Do you want to go live with him?

599
00:44:44,740 --> 00:44:47,265
It's gonna be okay. It'll pass.

600
00:44:48,220 --> 00:44:49,592
If this is what you're like when drunk,

601
00:44:49,990 --> 00:44:51,076
I'm not talking to you.

602
00:44:51,112 --> 00:44:54,014
Why? Just a goodnight kiss then.

603
00:44:54,276 --> 00:44:56,280
I warned you. Don't do this.
